    story: `<p>Kathmandu Valley's proximity to forested hills makes it one of Asia's most convenient mountain biking destinations. The northern rim—defined by Shivapuri Nagarjun National Park and its adjacent Nagarjun Forest Reserve—provides a tiered playground of dirt roads, jeep tracks, and forested singletrack that climbs from around 1,300 m in the valley to the Shivapuri Peak area at 2,732 m. Routes can be tailored for a relaxed three-hour outing or a full-day epic crossing from Kakani to Sundarijal.</p><h3>Key Routes</h3><p>The Budhanilkantha–Shivapuri–Sundarijal traverse follows the national park's northern edge on a mix of off-road track and forest path, passing waterfalls and rhododendron forest. The Nagarjun–Kakani loop climbs through the royal forest reserve to the Kakani hilltop at 2,070 m, renowned for its Himalayan panorama, before descending to Balaju. The Scar Route inside Shivapuri is considered the most technically demanding, featuring sustained climbs and rooty, rocky descents through dense jungle.</p><h3>Highlights</h3><ul><li>Singletrack through Shivapuri and Nagarjun national forests</li><li>Himalayan viewpoints at Kakani, Shivapuri, and Jamacho</li><li>Accessible from Thamel in under 30 minutes</li><li>Bike rental from Thamel shops: USD 10–25/day depending on spec</li><li>Best October–May; trails dry and grippy in autumn and early spring</li></ul>`,
