    name: "Canyoning Jalbire",
    category: "ADVENTURE_SPORTS",
    summary: "Jalbire Canyoning offers an exhilarating full-day descent of a narrow river canyon approximately 100 km from Kathmandu, featuring a dramatic 60-metre waterfall rappel, natural water slides, cliff jumps, and swim-throughs in crystalline pools. Situated near the Chitwan borderland, the site is accessible on the Prithvi Highway and combines easily with Pokhara or Chitwan itineraries. It is considered the most beginner-friendly canyoning destination in Nepal, suitable for adults and older children alike.",
    story: `<p>Jalbire emerged as Nepal's premier canyoning destination because it delivers all the classic elements of the sport—rappelling, sliding, jumping, and swimming—within a single canyon that requires no prior experience. The site's centrepiece is a tiered waterfall system culminating in a 60-metre rappel down a moss-covered cliff face into a jade-green plunge pool. The entire canyon descent takes four to six hours including safety briefings, gear fitting, and photography stops.</p><h3>The Canyon Experience</h3><p>Groups begin with a 12-metre starter cliff jump to test nerves before moving deeper into the canyon. A series of natural rock slides funnels participants into pools before the main rappel section arrives. The 60-metre waterfall rappel is conducted in two pitches with certified guides belaying from above and below, ensuring safety even for first-timers. After the descent, the canyon opens into a broad river valley where participants can swim before the return walk to the road.</p><h3>Highlights</h3><ul><li>60-metre main waterfall rappel (largest in Nepal's canyoning circuits)</li><li>Natural rock slides and cliff jumps up to 12 metres</li><li>Suitable for beginners including older children</li><li>Located 97–117 km from Pokhara and Kathmandu respectively</li><li>Best season: October–May; avoid peak monsoon</li><li>Full equipment (wetsuit, helmet, harness) provided by operators</li></ul>`,
